---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ScrollIndicator from '../../components/ScrollIndicator.astro';
import Quote from '../../components/Quote.astro';
---

<Layout>
    <ScrollIndicator />

    <div class="blog-summary">
        <nav class="breadcrumb">
            <a href="/blogs">← Back to Blogs</a>
        </nav>

        <header>
            <h1>Getting Started with Astro</h1>
            <div class="blog-meta">
                <p>Published: July 22, 2025</p>
            </div>
        </header>

        <section class="blog-content">
            <p>Astro is a new static site generator that offers some unique features. In this post, I'll walk you through setting up your first Astro project.</p>

            <h2>What is Astro?</h2>
            <p>Astro is a modern static site builder that allows you to use your favorite JavaScript framework (React, Vue, Svelte, etc.) while shipping less JavaScript to the browser. It's designed around content-focused websites where performance matters.</p>

            <h2>Installation</h2>
            <p>Getting started with Astro is easy. Just run the following command in your terminal:</p>

            <pre><code>npm create astro@latest</code></pre>

            <p>This will guide you through creating a new Astro project with a helpful interactive CLI.</p>

            <h2>Project Structure</h2>
            <p>A typical Astro project structure looks like this:</p>

            <pre><code>
├── public/
├── src/
│   ├── components/
│   ├── layouts/
│   └── pages/
├── astro.config.mjs
├── package.json
└── tsconfig.json
            </code></pre>

            <h2>Creating Pages</h2>
            <p>In Astro, each page is its own component. To create a new page, simply add a new .astro file in the src/pages directory. For example, to create a contact page, you would create src/pages/contact.astro.</p>

            <h2>Using Components</h2>
            <p>Astro allows you to use components from various frameworks. Here's an example of using a React component in an Astro file:</p>

            <pre><code>
---
import ReactCounter from '../components/ReactCounter.jsx';
---

&lt;html&gt;
  &lt;body&gt;
    &lt;ReactCounter client:load /&gt;
  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
            </code></pre>

            <h2>Conclusion</h2>
            <p>Astro offers a powerful and flexible approach to building websites. With its unique partial hydration system, you can build highly performant sites without sacrificing developer experience.</p>
        </section>
    </div>
</Layout>

